  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "DESIGN ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare engineering designs, calculations, drawings, and technical submissions in accordance with applicable codes and standards</p></li><li><p>Perform design analysis and checks to ensure safety, constructability, and compliance</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal project teams, consultants, and contractors on design matters</p></li><li><p>Review technical documents, drawings, and specifications</p></li><li><p>Provide design support during construction, including addressing technical queries and site issues</p></li><li><p>Assist with submissions to relevant authorities where required</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper design records and documentation</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Civil Engineering / Structural Engineering / Geotechnical Engineering or related discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2 years</strong> of relevant engineering design experience</p></li><li><p>Proficient in engineering design software and drafting tools (e.g. AutoCAD or equivalent)</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore design codes, standards, and statutory requirements</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and as part of a multidisciplinary team</p></li></ul>",
